<section id="To_clone_a_Virtual_Machine_VMware_Virtual_Machines_only1" remap="TID_15532">
	<title>Cloning a Virtual Machine (VMware Virtual Machines Only)</title>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Clone a Virtual Machine</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Virtual Machines</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, and check the virtual machine you want to clone.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2007.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Lifecycle)</guilabel>, and then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2339.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Clone selected item)</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Fill in the options as shown in <guilabel>To Provision</guilabel> from a template using the provided dialogs. Be sure to check the <guilabel>Catalog Tab</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Schedule the request on the <guilabel>Schedule</guilabel> tab.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guilabel>Submit</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>